<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Students who have taken advanced or college-level courses in high school and scored a 3 or above in the College Board Advanced Placement tests are responsible for having scores forwarded to the Registrar's Office at the College to apply for college credit and/or advanced placement. The amount of credit allocated is determined by the department of the subject in which the test was taken.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.csm.edu/Academics/Academic_Catalog/" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

